summary: So apparently within The Moomin comics, the Muddler actually had another son called the Fuddler- And I have spent my entire week...
caption:
So apparently within The Moomin comics, the Muddler actually had another son called the Fuddler-

And I have spent my entire week coming up with headcanons for him-

The Fuddler is Muddler and Fuzzy’s second child and Sniff’s younger brother by quite a few years. Fuddler was entirely unplanned, but not unwanted, as his poor parents had been searching tirelessly for his missing older brother when he was conceived. Fuddler is all kinds of sheltered, since his parents very rarely let him out of their sight and usually kept him in a baby harness, their poor hearts just wouldn’t be able to handle the loss of another child. As such, he was endlessly loved and doted upon, and spent much of his childhood longing to meet the older brother that his parents were always looking for.

Sniff was jealous of Fuddler as soon as they met, believing him to be the favorite, seeing as how their parents didn’t lose him, and he was ever so similar to their father. It didn’t help that Fuddler was constantly following him around, asking him questions, requesting to play with him, and wanting to show Sniff his drawings. After a while though, Sniff came to realize just how sincere his brothers affection for him was, and decided that he wanted to be someone Fuddler could look up to. From that point on, their bond was sealed in iron, and Fuddler has carried an intense hero worship for his brother ever since!

Some fun facts:

- He carries a pack of crayons with him wherever he goes, and likes to draw on whatever he can find.

- Has the best memory of anyone in his family and is always reminding his father of important dates and other such things

- He’s VERY scared of Snufkin

- Is incredibly sweet, and wants everyone to get along, but he can YELL. Especially if you ever call his brothers coolness into question.

- Since he was pretty sheltered as a child, he didn’t really hang out with kids his age very much, and doesn’t really know how to do things like swim, or make flower crowns, or handle social situations normally

And I have spent my entire week coming up with headcanons for him-
